19 requires the owner of a cemetery to take certain specific actions to ensure that a
20 cemetery is kept in an orderly condition.
21 Existing law provides for the establishment, operation and maintenance of
22 veterans’ cemeteries and sets forth the eligibility requirements for the interment of
23 veterans in such cemeteries. (NRS 417.210) Section 6 of this bill expands the
24 eligibility requirements to include certain veterans who were members of a reserve
25 component of the National Guard or who received a commemorative plaque or urn
26 furnished by the United States Department of Veterans Affairs. Section 6 also
27 requires the Director of the Department of Veterans Services to charge a fee for: (1)
28 the interment of a veteran made eligible under the expanded criteria set forth in
29 section 6; and (2) a headstone or marker provided by the Department for certain
30 veterans made eligible for interment under the expanded criteria set forth in section
31 6.
